      • direction

        public GraphConfigurator<V,E> direction(java.util.function.Function<E,java.util.Comparator<V>> lowToHigh)
        Description copied from interface: GraphConfigurator
        This method accepts a function to create a comparator from an edge, over the vertices associated with that edge. The result of the application of this comparator will be used to determine the direction of that edge, with the semantics described by the GraphConfigurator.direction(Comparator) method. The function is only applied at most once per creation of an edge.
        Specified by:
        direction in interface GraphConfigurator<V,E>
